<Content_wSideColumn ID="x63263" Name="FAQ" Layout="general_content.xsl"><Title type="string" label="Title" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="true">Frequently Asked Questions</Title><Abstract type="string" label="Abstract" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="true">questions answered</Abstract><xPower Type="GroupStart" GroupStart="" Name="SideColumn" label="L/R Column" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false" Expanded="false"><MoveLeft type="boolean" label="Toggle column right or left (right is default)" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false">false</MoveLeft><xPower Type="Component" Component="" Name="ImageComponent" label="Image Component" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false" CompTypes="LeftColumnImageComponent"/><xPower Type="Component" Component="" Name="TextComponent" label="Text Component" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false" CompTypes="ColumnTextComponent"/><fbookTop type="boolean" label="Put facebook at top of page" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false">false</fbookTop><fbookStatus type="string" label="Facebook ID#" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false"></fbookStatus><fbookDisplayed type="string" label="Number of facebook messages to display" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false">1</fbookDisplayed></xPower><BodyCopy type="dhtml" label="Body Copy" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false"><![CDATA[<div>
<p><span style="color: #666666; line-height: 18px; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;"><span style="line-height: 21px; display: inline;"><em style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;"><strong style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;">Q</strong></em></span></span></p>
<p align="justify" style="line-height: 1.5em; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;"><em style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;"> -<strong> Will students be able to print to campus printers while connected to the wireless network?</strong></em></span></p>
<p align="justify" style="line-height: 1.5em; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;"> </p>
<p style="line-height: 1.5em; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;"><strong style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;">A - Yes, students will be able to print to campus network printers.  Visit <em style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;"><a href="http://www.byui.edu/HelpDesk/StudentTech/default.htm" style="text-decoration: underline; color: #00254a; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;" target="_self">Student Tech Home</a> </em>for a wireless printing tutorial</strong>.</span></p>
<p style="line-height: 1.5em; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;"> </p>
<p style="line-height: 1.5em; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;"> </p>
<p align="justify" style="line-height: 1.5em; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;"><em style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;"><strong style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;">Q</strong> - Why are there cheaper laptops in other stores compared to the recommended BYU-Idaho models?</em></span></p>
<p style="line-height: 1.5em; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;"> </p>
<p style="line-height: 1.5em; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;"><strong style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;">A - The recommended BYU-Idaho models are business class laptops and not consumer models.  In short, they are built better, using higher quality, standard, components.  The University sought to secure units that would last for the duration of your educational experience at BYU-I.</strong></span></p>
<p style="line-height: 1.5em; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;"> </p>
<p style="line-height: 1.5em; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;"><strong style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;">Q</strong><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;"> - </span><em style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;">Why are HP and Apple the only models available through the bookstore?</em></p>
<p style="line-height: 1.5em; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;"> </p>
<p style="line-height: 1.5em; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;"><strong style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;">A - The university received bids from serveral other manufactures.  HP and Apple were selected because of their willingness to provide the needed quality for the most resonable price.</strong></span></p>
<p style="line-height: 1.5em; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;"> </p>
<p style="line-height: 1.5em; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;"> </p>
<p style="line-height: 1.5em; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;"><strong style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;">Q -</strong> <em style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;">Do I have to purchase an Apple computer?</em></span></p>
<p style="line-height: 1.5em; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;"> </p>
<p style="line-height: 1.5em; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;"><strong style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;">A -</strong> There may be a platform that your particular college requires.  Detailed information can be found under the "<a href="http://www.byui.edu/Laptop/requirement.htm" style="text-decoration: underline; color: #00254a; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;" target="_parent">Laptop Requirement</a>" regarding your major's requirements.  A Windows laptop will meet the needs of the vast majority of students, particularly for those majors where another brand requirement has not  been specified.  Where there is no specification students may pick the platform they prefer (Windows or Apple).</span></p>
<p style="line-height: 1.5em; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;"> </p>
<p style="line-height: 1.5em; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;"> </p>
<p style="line-height: 1.5em; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;"><strong style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;">Q</strong> - <em style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;">Why are students required to have laptops if they are not used in every class?</em></span></p>
<p style="line-height: 1.5em; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;"> </p>
<p style="line-height: 1.5em; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;"><strong style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;">A - Laptop benefits extend away from the classroom, but will also include an every growing number of classroom uses as the requirement matures and more courses grow into the use of this educational option.</strong></span></p>
<p style="line-height: 1.5em; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;"><strong style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;"> </strong></span></p>
<p style="line-height: 1.5em; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;"><strong style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;"> </strong></span></p>
<p style="line-height: 1.5em; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;"><strong style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;">Q</strong> - My major does not seem technical, why should I have a laptop<em style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;">?</em></span></p>
<p style="line-height: 1.5em; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;"> </p>
<p style="line-height: 1.5em; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;"><strong style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px;">A - Every field increasingly depends upon technology.  Owning and working with a laptop increases personal abilities to work with and understand technology in ways that casual use does not.  Laptops can assist in preparing students for the competitive job marketplace.</strong></span></p>
<p><span style="line-height: 18px;"><br /></span></p>
